## Findings on `DatabaseVersion.make(2025, 3)` for InterSystems IRIS

### 1. `DatabaseVersion.make(year, minor)` semantics
**File:** `hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/dialect/DatabaseVersion.java:28-37`

```java
static DatabaseVersion make(Integer major, Integer minor) {
    return make( major, minor, 0 );
}

static DatabaseVersion make(Integer major, Integer minor, Integer micro) {
    return new SimpleDatabaseVersion( major, minor, micro );
}
```

`DatabaseVersion.make(major, minor)` creates a `SimpleDatabaseVersion` where the values map directly to `java.sql.DatabaseMetaData.getDatabaseMajorVersion()` and `getDatabaseMinorVersion()`. The `micro` defaults to 0. So `DatabaseVersion.make(2025, 3)` creates major=2025, minor=3, micro=0.

### 2. How other dialects set their minimum version

| Dialect | MINIMUM_VERSION | Actual Database Version |
|---------|-----------------|------------------------|
| PostgreSQLDialect | `DatabaseVersion.make(14)` | PostgreSQL 14 |
| MySQLDialect | `DatabaseVersion.make(8)` | MySQL 8.x |
| SQLServerDialect | `DatabaseVersion.make(12, 0)` | SQL Server 2014 (v12.0) |
| OracleDialect | `DatabaseVersion.make(19)` | Oracle 19c |
| MariaDBDialect | `DatabaseVersion.make(10, 6)` | MariaDB 10.6 |
| CockroachDialect | `DatabaseVersion.make(23, 2)` | CockroachDB v23.2 |

### 3. Version comparison in Dialect base class
**File:** `hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/dialect/Dialect.java:373-385`

```java
protected void checkVersion() {
    final var version = getVersion();
