**VERDICT: Confirmed - version 2025.3 follows InterSystems IRIS' actual versioning scheme.**

InterSystems IRIS uses year-based release naming (e.g., 2023.1, 2024.1, 2024.2, 2024.3, etc.). The JDBC driver returns this via `DatabaseMetaData.getDatabaseMajorVersion()` returning the year (2025) and `getDatabaseMinorVersion()` returning the release number (3). This is consistent with how other dialects like CockroachDB (`make(23, 2)`) use year-based major versions.

